# Conda — Project Prompt

## What Conda Is

Conda is a privacy-first AI intelligence layer for financial advisors and accountants. It lets advisors upload their entire book of business — anonymized with Client IDs only, no PII — and have an open-ended conversation with a senior analyst (Claude) who has memorized every portfolio, tax situation, and risk profile.

Conda is **not** a proposal generator or a form-filling tool. It is an always-on intelligence layer. The advisor talks to it like a colleague, and it produces real deliverables (decks, spreadsheets, PDFs, charts) directly in the conversation — built from the firm's own templates.

## Core Architecture

### Privacy Model — Two-File Architecture

1. **Client Directory** (File 1 — PRIVATE): Contains Client ID, Full Name, email, phone, company. Parsed and stored **only in browser memory / localStorage**. NEVER sent to any API.

2. **Book Data** (File 2 — SENT TO AI): Contains Client ID, Age, Holdings, Tax Info, Risk Profile. Anonymized — no PII. Serialized into the system prompt.

The AI reasons on anonymous data. Real names are re-attached locally for file downloads. PII never touches the wire.

### PII Safety Net

If the advisor types a client name in chat, the system silently replaces it with the Client ID before sending to the API (`sanitizeForAPI` in `chat-interface.tsx`).

### File Generation Privacy

When Claude generates a file (PPTX, XLSX, PDF), it uses Client IDs in tool payloads. The `/api/generate-file` endpoint receives a `client_map` from the browser and re-injects real names right before file creation.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 14, App Router, TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4, dark theme
- **AI**: Anthropic Claude API (configurable via `ANTHROPIC_MODEL` env var, defaults to `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`)
- **File Parsing**: `papaparse` (CSV), `xlsx` (Excel book data), `mammoth` (DOCX), `pdf-parse` (PDF), `jszip` (PPTX)
- **File Generation**: `pptxgenjs` (PowerPoint), `exceljs` (Excel), `jspdf` + `jspdf-autotable` (PDF)
- **Charts**: `recharts` (inline interactive charts)
- **Markdown**: `react-markdown` + `remark-gfm`
- **Deployment**: Vercel (serverless, streaming)

## Application Flow

```
Landing Page (/) → Mode Select → Upload (two files) → Privacy Gate → Chat
                                                                       ↓
                                                            Settings (/settings/style)
```

1. **Mode Selection**: Financial Advisor or Accountant
2. **Upload**: Private Client Directory (optional) + anonymized Book Data
3. **Privacy Gate**: Animated data-flow visualization
4. **Chat**: Split-panel — sidebar with book summary + client table; main chat with streaming AI, tool use, inline charts, file downloads

## Skill Files (Document Templates)

Advisors upload sample documents (PPTX, PDF, XLSX, DOCX, TXT) at `/settings/style`. These are **skill files** — real examples of the firm's deliverables.

**How they work:**
- The full extracted text of each document is stored in `localStorage` under `conda_skill_files`
- On every chat message, the full text is injected into the system prompt so Claude can see the exact structure, section order, slide layouts, column formats, and content
- When the advisor asks Claude to build a proposal/deck/worksheet, Claude references these skill files and replicates the structure with new client data
- If multiple skill files could apply, Claude asks which one to use as the base

**This is NOT style analysis.** The AI reads the actual documents and builds from them — matching section order, heading patterns, slide structure, column layouts, and formatting conventions.

### Supported formats for skill files:
- `.pptx` — Slides extracted as text via ZIP/XML parsing
- `.pdf` — Text extracted via `pdf-parse`
- `.xlsx` / `.xls` — Sheets/rows/cells extracted via `exceljs`
- `.docx` — Text extracted via `mammoth`
- `.txt` / `.md` — Direct text

All extraction happens server-side at `/api/parse-document`.

## Chat & Tool Use

### How messages flow (`components/chat-interface.tsx`):

- **Initial Scan**: Auto-fires on first mount — Claude reviews the book unprompted (SSE streaming)
- **User Messages**: Sent with `enableFileTools: true` → `/api/chat` returns JSON with `text`, `tool_calls`, `usage`
- **Tool Processing**: `render_chart` → Recharts inline; `generate_pptx/xlsx/pdf` → async `/api/generate-file` → download card in chat

### File Generation Tools (`lib/tools.ts`):

- `generate_pptx` — PowerPoint with multiple slide layouts
- `generate_xlsx` — Excel with formulas, formatting, freeze panes
- `generate_pdf` — PDF with sections, tables, footers
- `render_chart` — Inline interactive charts

### All deliverables are generated in chat.
There is no separate "Generate Report" button. The advisor asks Claude in natural language and gets files back inline.

## API Routes

| Route | Purpose | Max Duration |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/chat` | Claude conversation (streaming + tool use) | 120s |
| `/api/generate-file` | File generation from tool calls | 60s |
| `/api/parse-document` | Text extraction from uploaded files | 30s |

